Date: Fri 12 Feb 2010
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2010; 23(7) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=8948>


African horse sickness, Ghana
-----------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 12 Feb 2010 from Dr Enoch
Boye-Mensah Koney, Acting Director, Veterinary Services Department,
Ministry of Food and Agriculture, Accra, Ghana

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 18 Jan 2010
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 2 Feb 2010
Report date: 12 Feb 2010
Date submitted to OIE: 12 Feb 2010
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: June 1985
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: African horse sickness virus
Serotype 2
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Accra Polo Grounds, Accra Metropolitan Assembly, Greater Accra
Date of start of the outbreak: 18 Jan 2010
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Species: Equidae
Susceptible: 185
Cases: 30
Deaths: 30
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0

Outbreak statistics
Species: Equidae
Apparent morbidity rate: 16.22 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 16.22 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 100.00 percent
Proportion susceptible animals lost*: 16.22 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction,
and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied:
- no vaccination
- no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Institute of Animal Health, Pirbright
(United Kingdom) (OIE's Reference Laboratory)
Species: Equidae
Test: polymerase chain reaction (PCR)
Test date: 2 Feb 2010
Result: positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

